Investigate ideas, pursue plans
Under Instructions From State Trustees.
One of Collingwood's most intriguing, individual properties - on a generous allotment - creates a captivating opportunity to consider re-development concepts or undertake a full scale renovation project, STCA. Either strategy suggests a rewarding outcome, complemented by the appeal of the location, close to schools, trams, shopping and within easy reach of the CBD. A warehouse style image introduces current day spaces comprising a dual level floor-plan of six principal rooms defined by timber floors, remarkable originality and an obvious readiness for revival or replacement. Flexible living, dining, accommodation or studio spaces accompanied by a basic kitchen and bathroom define the structure, while north easterly outdoor areas conclude with a garage and huge storage shed accessed from a convenient rear lane. An inner city property that's loaded with possibilities.

Description:
Collingwood the contemporary way
Northern light adds a significant natural asset to the already impressive credentials of this designer dual level apartment. Spaces that clearly make a strong statement of style include a living/dining area accompanied by a Caesar stone open plan kitchen and a sunny balcony beneath an elegant cafe awning. Reverse cycle heating/cooling, a study zone and an attractively appointed bathroom complete the lower level while above, two bright bedrooms, each with built in robes and their own heating/cooling, share a second, semi ensuite central bathroom. Secure storage cage and garaging accessed from second frontage to Budd Street mean convenience matches comfort and enhances an opportunity with evident lifestyle or investment appeal. The location makes its own substantial contribution too. Quiet, yet so close to Smith Street trams and the area's vibrant retail and restaurant scene, the stage is set for inner city enjoyment.

Forthcoming auction (prior offers invited). Description:
Inspired Warehouse Conversion by Carr Design
Featured in Belle magazine, this stunning warehouse conversion successfully marries contemporary design with an industrial, cool aesthetic. Positioned in the iconic Foy and Gibson precinct, the warehouse has been extensively remodeled and refurbished by one of Australia's most respected interior design and architecture firms, Carr Design.
Exposing the building's rich architectural heritage which includes original timber beams and trusses, Carr Design have inserted a new structure into the existing form which adds two loft-style bedrooms and a rooftop deck. This insertion creates a logical flow between the interior spaces, and adds two large voids flooding the living areas with natural light.
Upon entry is a large flexible space which can easily serve as a study, second living area, or a spacious home office. Original timber floorboards lead through to a stylish kitchen - with ample storage and integrated appliances - and an 11metre long bench, which can seat up to 12 people. Towards the rear is an open plan living area, which has soaring six metre ceiling heights, built-in shelving and dramatic floodlights. Two windows look out to the beguiling urban streetscape, providing an ever-changing kaleidoscope of colour and texture.
Upstairs features two spacious bedrooms both with built-in wardrobes. A contemporary, fully tiled bathroom which separates the bedrooms adds to the industrial feel. A spectacular rooftop deck has expansive views overlooking the city skyline, Studley Park and onwards to the Dandenongs.
Additional features include security entrance with intercom, secure car parking, heating, innovative design initiatives such as elevated flooring to conceal services and a concealed laundry and scullery. With Gertrude and Smith Street culture at your doorstep, the MCG around the corner, and the CBD just a short stroll away, inner-city living doesn't get much better than this.
Insights: 29 other 2 bedroom house in COLLINGWOOD have recently been sold.

Description:
EXTRA SPACIOUS, PERIOD CHARACTER
Looking for family-size living close to schools, Smith Street and Queens Parade? This late Victorian residence with spacious rooms and a wealth of period ornament offers just that! Renovated to combine modern comfort with 19th century decorative detail ( deep cornice work and niches to the high-ceilinged entrance hall), the house offers three double BRs (ensuite to main), a large study/4th bedroom, an expansive living/dining room opening to the sunny courtyard, solid timber kitchen, a tiled family bathroom, laundry and powder room. This light-filled property includes off-street parking via side drive, and features ducted heating, air conditioning and exceptional storage space.

Description:
WHAT A TRANSFORMATION!
An imaginative renovation has optimised space and light in this free-standing Victorian cottage. The main entry is from a side pathway to a vast open plan living and dining area with a well-equipped kitchen set to one side. Timber stairs ascend to a mezzanine level study under the soaring ceiling. The entertaining zone flows out through multifold doors to a private courtyard, with rolladoor access from a right of way. The main bedroom, with a door to the front verandah, incorporates part of the original nineteenth century hallway, now a north-facing gallery opening to the second double bedroom and a fully-tiled bathroom with separate bath and shower. Features of this stylish city-fringe property include a concealed laundry, quality appliances, split-system airconditioning and ceiling fans and polished concrete floors.

Description:
Hidden Gem
Hidden behind the beautiful Italianate facade of the original Collingwood Post Office (circa 1891) is this private and quiet 1 bedroom apartment. Generous in size this wonderful apartment is soaked in natural light with a sensational alfresco balcony great for enjoying with friends and family. Large open plan living/dining area, funky stone kitchen with stainless steel appliances, generous light filled bedroom (BIR's), sleek bathroom and euro laundry and being much larger than expected all add up to make this one great home. This apartment offers the best of both worlds, allowing you to enjoy the cosmopolitan lifestyle that Smith St has to offer on your doorstep, while being able to come home and be securely tucked away behind this magnificent building with secure intercom entry and basement parking with lift access. The ultimate lifestyle with cafes, the nightlife and the city tram at your doorstep.
-Superb location
-Generous size
-Heritage facade
-Great balcony and outlook
-Sunny and bright
-Secure entry, and basement garaging.
For one lucky purchaser the search will be over, this is a must inspect.
